1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:13,567
<i>I already let him have the movie
world.</i>

2
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:16,467
<i>Calabari needs a change of
leadership.</i>

3
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,633
<i>Now he wants to mess with
politics too?</i>

4
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:20,900
<i> I just got the news.</i>

5
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,433
<i>I'm not your family, you don't
need to sympathize me.</i>

6
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:25,367
<i> Those robbers in the movie...</i>

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>they're just like the ones who
held up the bank.</i>

8
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:28,833
<i>Conde, I won't let you take the
law</i>

9
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:29,767
<i> into your own hands.</i>

10
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,067
<i>You're suspended until you're
ready!</i>

11
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,233
<i> What did you say?</i>

12
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>Don't force the girl if she
doesn't want to go.</i>

13
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,867
<i>Hey, stop! You don't want to...</i>

14
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:44,333
Wait a minute, Grandmother.

15
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:47,867
What?

16
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,767
What did you say earlier?

17
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,567
Wait, Grandmother.

18
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:07,100
There, Grandmother.

19
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,767
Look at this.

20
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:11,100
<i> Good day, Bros!</i>

21
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:12,867
<i>You won't be at a disadvantage.</i>

22
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:16,400
Hey, those are the same guys
from that documentary.

23
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,067
Yes, Grandmother.

24
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:22,067
Boss had a movie back then
titled Maligno Robbers.

25
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,800
Check out the villain's mask in
that movie.

26
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:35,433
So what's with the masks?

27
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,067
Grandmother, they're the exact
same masks

28
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,200
the bank robbers wore.

29
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,633
What?

30
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,533
I'm still looking for a copy of
the film, Sir.

31
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:54,800
But just look at that.

32
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:58,833
The masks are identical to the
ones used in the robbery.

33
00:01:58,967 --> 00:02:01,133
Enriquez...

34
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:03,267
Most likely, the bank robbers

35
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,367
saw that film

36
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:08,033
and were inspired to use those
masks.

37
00:02:08,167 --> 00:02:10,867
There's nothing to this,
Sergeant Enriquez.

38
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,800
What? You think Victor Santiago

39
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,467
is involved in the robbery?

40
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,967
Yes, Sir.

41
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:22,067
It could be him or someone
involved in the film.

42
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,567
Enriquez, this movie is more
than 20 years old!

43
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:28,267
But Sir, I really have a strong
feeling about this!

44
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,600
I don't know how, but I believe

45
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:33,767
Boss's film is connected to the
bank robbery.

46
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:36,333
You know what I think, Enriquez?

47
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:39,567
I think you're just wasting my
time.

48
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,067
- Now, get out.
- But, Sir...

49
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,133
I said get out!

50
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:03,467
Freeze!

51
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,767
Put your hands up!

52
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:25,767
So, what did your boss say?

53
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,133
He wouldn't believe me,
Grandmother.

54
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:32,900
He said I was just wasting time.

55
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:36,400
But do you believe

56
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:40,000
Amo is involved in the robbery?

57
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:48,500
It's hard to believe this is
just coincidence,

58
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:53,567
or that the robbers were merely
inspired by Amo's movie,

59
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,733
like the chief said.

60
00:03:58,467 --> 00:04:00,567
If it's not Amo,

61
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:05,767
then maybe he knows someone
involved in that robbery.

62
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,633
What's your plan now?

63
00:04:12,033 --> 00:04:15,533
Station 12 is handling the bank
robbery case.

64
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,267
I'll request a transfer there.

65
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,067
Maybe they'll believe me.

66
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:35,700
Transparency, service,
and accountability.

67
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:38,667
I will hide nothing from you.

68
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,567
I will serve you.

69
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:45,467
And if ever you see me make
a mistake,

70
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,300
just tell me...

71
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:50,867
I'll step down from the office
myself.

72
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:52,800
Oh, Sir...

73
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:56,533
You're known as the boss
of Filipino action films.

74
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:59,900
Why enter the world of politics?

75
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:03,967
Just like the characters I play
in movies,

76
00:05:04,133 --> 00:05:05,833
I can't stay silent

77
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:09,400
when people are being oppressed.

78
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:13,933
So you mean the people of
Calabari are oppressed?

79
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:18,333
How many terms has
Mayor Joaquin Guerrero served?

80
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:22,267
What has he really contributed
to the people of Calabari?

81
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,900
There is.

82
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:31,633
There's education, housing,
and free hospitalization.

83
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:35,667
Housing for a few.

84
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:40,467
Education, but no jobs waiting.

85
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:45,000
Free hospitalization, but
expensive medicine.

86
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,733
Son of a duck, really.

87
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:50,867
It was weighed and found
lacking.

88
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:54,333
Good day to you, Mayor.

89
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:55,633
Why?

90
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:59,800
Do you think you can give what
is lacking that you're saying?

91
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:05,033
A man from the movie industry,

92
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:11,100
with no political experience?

93
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,033
Thank you! Until next time!

94
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:16,600
Ma'am!

95
00:06:17,767 --> 00:06:19,167
Lumpia! This is different.

96
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,567
And we also have shanghai.

97
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,833
Do you want some?

98
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:24,433
Sergeant Enriquez, good morning!

99
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:26,333
Good morning, Abi.

100
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:27,700
- Yes!
- What are we selling today?

101
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,933
Oh, Ma'am, you'll love this.

102
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:33,267
Lumpia with a twist.

103
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:36,933
With a twist.

104
00:06:37,067 --> 00:06:38,733
- What kind of twist?
- Smell it.

105
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:41,167
It has an egg inside!

106
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:44,133
Wow! Right!

107
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:45,533
Oh my gosh.

108
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:48,800
You really are the lumpia queen
of Station 12.

109
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:49,933
Of course, of course.

110
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:51,700
I'll get two later.
Just save them for me, okay?

111
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:52,767
Copy, Ma'am.

112
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,467
Time really flies, right?

113
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,200
You've been here six months at
Station 12.

114
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,367
How are you?

115
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,967
I'm fine.

116
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,333
Yes, time does fly.

117
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:05,933
All right, I'll go ahead.

118
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,300
- See you later.
- Oh, okay.

119
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:09,400
Thank you!

120
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,567
Okay.

121
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,633
Chief, good morning.

122
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,100
Have some lumpia.

123
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:17,967
Different flavors,
for your lunch.

124
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:21,333
Thanks again, Sir,
for the copy of Amo's film.

125
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:22,567
I'll call you again

126
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,200
if I need anything.

127
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,700
Thank you.

128
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:37,267
<i> Good day, Bros!</i>

129
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,200
<i>You won't be at a disadvantage!</i>

130
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,133
<i> Don't be hardheaded!</i>

131
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:42,833
<i> We just need to get rich!</i>

132
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,833
<i> Good day, Bros!</i>

133
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,267
<i>You won't be at a disadvantage.</i>

134
00:07:50,433 --> 00:07:52,867
<i> Don't be hardheaded!</i>

135
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:57,167
<i> We just need to get rich!</i>

136
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,500
It's not just the mask
that's the same.

137
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,067
Even the robber's dialogue

138
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,600
matches Amo's film exactly.

139
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:10,200
Maybe the mayor forgot

140
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:14,400
he also came from the movie
world.

141
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:18,233
He had no experience either when
he started.

142
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:20,667
Right? He just learned along the
way.

143
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,200
Experience is not the issue

144
00:08:23,367 --> 00:08:26,333
if one is willing to serve.

145
00:08:26,467 --> 00:08:29,733
By the way, what's the status of
the San Isidro bank robbery?

146
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:31,933
Have the suspects been caught?

147
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,267
The police are doing their job.

148
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:37,200
You know what, Victor? Stay out
of this.

149
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:41,867
Just because you know how to
investigate in movies

150
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,133
doesn't mean you know how in
real life.

151
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,867
At least in my films,

152
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,167
crimes get solved.

153
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:53,500
Ma'am, what's that?

154
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,833
You look serious.

155
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,667
Noble...

156
00:08:58,133 --> 00:09:00,700
I thought that when I
transferred to Station 12,

157
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:04,600
I'd be included in the San
Isidro robbery investigation.

158
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:07,600
They don't believe my theory.

159
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:10,300
But maybe once they see this,

160
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:14,067
the investigation team will
finally believe me.

161
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:16,333
Enriquez!

162
00:09:16,467 --> 00:09:21,067
We'll only believe you if you
admit we had a thing.

163
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:24,133
Ma'am, was Lieutenant Garcia
your ex?

164
00:09:24,267 --> 00:09:25,767
In his mind.

165
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,433
Sir...

166
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:30,067
You know, I found a copy of
Amo's film...

167
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,900
the one I told you about.

168
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:33,167
Not only are the masks
identical,

169
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,733
even the dialogue is the same.

170
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:38,967
Well, Enriquez...

171
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:42,267
We followed up on that lead.

172
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:45,467
Amo's was in the Visayas when
the robbery happened.

173
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,167
He's not on our suspect list.

174
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,500
Did you even bother to check

175
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:51,567
where the masks are now?

176
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:52,867
Wait, Enriquez.

177
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,133
Are you telling us

178
00:09:54,267 --> 00:09:56,200
how to do our jobs?

179
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,067
What if we get back together...

180
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:00,733
are you going to decide
everything?

181
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,067
Where the kid goes to school?
What color the fridge should be?

182
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,100
Are you going to control me
again?

183
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:07,000
I'm just asking, Sir.

184
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,167
Hey, Sergeant.

185
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:10,733
You're not part of the
investigation group

186
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:12,133
to ask questions.

187
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:18,133
But if you want to be the
girlfriend of the team leader...

188
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:22,267
I mean, leader of the
investigation group,

189
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,600
maybe we can talk.

190
00:10:26,133 --> 00:10:27,633
No but thank you, Sir.

191
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,133
That's just how she is...

192
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,033
shy.

193
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,333
But she does have a crush on me,

194
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:38,833
it's just that there's too many
people.

195
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:45,667
Oh, Joaquin, Victor...

196
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,133
Let's not do this here.

197
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:50,400
It's embarrassing in front of
our media friends.

198
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:54,300
You're not just insulting me,
Victor,

199
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:58,133
you're insulting the Calabari
police force.

200
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:02,300
I'm not insulting the police.

201
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:07,500
But over a hundred criminal
cases remain unresolved

202
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:09,967
since the Mayor took office.

203
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:12,700
Why is that? What's the reason?

204
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:17,500
My fellow citizens, please
excuse my daddy

205
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:20,400
and my godfather Victor.

206
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:22,333
They just missed each other.

207
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:25,067
But the truth is,

208
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,200
these two are godbrothers.

209
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,667
Right?

210
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:32,767
We returned each other's candles
a long time ago.

211
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,867
Oh, he's the only one who gave
back the candle.

212
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,433
As far as I'm concerned,

213
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:39,700
even if we have a bit of a rift,

214
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:44,033
he's still my friend and
godbrother.

215
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,033
May the best man win.

216
00:11:50,267 --> 00:11:52,733
The best man will win.

217
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:02,167
Sergeant Enriquez...

218
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:05,300
you requested a transfer here
to Station 12

219
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,633
because according to you,

220
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:10,367
there was discrimination at your
previous precinct...

221
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:13,300
but that's not your
real reason, is it?

222
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:14,500
I just want to help

223
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:16,767
in the robbery investigation,
Sir.

224
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:21,433
Robbery or your
godmother's death?

225
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:25,067
I know you have...

226
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,667
a personal involvement
in this case.

227
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:32,100
That's why I'm the best person
for the job, Sir.

228
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:35,000
Because I'll do everything
just to solve this case.

229
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,433
That's exactly what Lieutenant
Conde told me

230
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:44,933
when he asked to handle the
case.

231
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:47,000
But I told him no.

232
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,167
That's why I suspended him.

233
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,200
Sergeant Enriquez,

234
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:54,900
my answer is still a no.

235
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:59,833
You can help by doing the job
I assigned to you.

236
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:03,100
So I'm assigning you to patrol.

237
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,933
Permission to leave, Sir.

238
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,667
- For Calabari!
- Yes!

239
00:13:29,633 --> 00:13:32,700
Okay then, Victor,
we'll head out.

240
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,833
Joaquin still has to file.

241
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:37,200
Okay, let's catch up soon.

242
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:38,467
Of course, let's do that.

243
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,167
Hey, you know what,

244
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:42,667
why don't you all come with us?

245
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,800
Join us so you can witness

246
00:13:44,933 --> 00:13:48,167
El Hepe file his candidacy.

247
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:50,633
Come on, let's go!

248
00:13:50,767 --> 00:13:53,300
- Victor. All right.
- I'll follow.

249
00:13:55,133 --> 00:13:56,833
- Godfather.
- What?

250
00:13:56,967 --> 00:13:58,667
Please be patient with dad.

251
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:01,367
Of course.

252
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,700
I've noticed you're getting
more and more buff.

253
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:06,467
Oh, I'll just ask you
something...

254
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:09,933
how's Calabari's number one
councilor doing?

255
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:11,567
Doing fine, Godfather.

256
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,633
Thank you for asking.

257
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:15,933
But, Godfather...

258
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:18,867
I know that you and dad
had a misunderstanding

259
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,033
but I know you share
a common goal,

260
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:25,300
to improve our city's condition.

261
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:27,067
So in the coming election,

262
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:30,867
let's leave the decision
to the people.

263
00:14:32,767 --> 00:14:36,700
You know, you're so different
from your dad.

264
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,467
Keep it up, all right?

265
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,633
- Will do, Godfather.
- All right then.

266
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:51,700
Okay.

267
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:54,133
- Take care, Sir.
- Okay.

268
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:57,400
Go ahead, Sir.

269
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:59,033
Take care.

270
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:00,967
Take care, take care.

271
00:15:03,733 --> 00:15:05,500
You know, Ma'am,

272
00:15:05,633 --> 00:15:08,667
now I get why you want
to be an investigator.

273
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:11,133
There's barely anything
happening on patrol.

274
00:15:11,267 --> 00:15:13,533
Sometimes there is.

275
00:15:13,667 --> 00:15:16,033
How about you,
what department do you want?

276
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:21,767
Me? I want SWAT,
there's action-packed stuff.

277
00:15:23,133 --> 00:15:24,533
Because ever since,

278
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,833
I've always wanted
to be an investigator.

279
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,500
Because of Amo's movies,
of course.

280
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,533
Ironic, isn't it?

281
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:34,200
You want to be an investigator
because of Amo...

282
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,300
yet now you want
to investigate him?

283
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:37,800
That's not what I meant.

284
00:15:37,933 --> 00:15:39,467
I just want to know
if he's connected

285
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,233
to the bank robbery.

286
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:44,133
If Lieutenant Conde hears about
that,

287
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:46,067
he's definitely going too.

288
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,400
Wasn't that where
his girlfriend died?

289
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:55,433
Have you talked to him about it?

290
00:15:57,733 --> 00:15:59,433
Not yet.

291
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:02,767
Ever since I transferred
to Station 12,

292
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:04,833
he's gone awol.

293
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,033
So that's why...

294
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,700
Oh.

295
00:16:13,633 --> 00:16:17,400
License, registration, and
official receipt, Boss.

296
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:23,300
That whole incident really
affected him, right?

297
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,367
Okay.

298
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,633
Thank you.
Be careful.

299
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:31,933
- Sir, take care.
- Thank you.

300
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,167
Take care.

301
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:45,167
Amo's assistant just messaged.

302
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:48,033
She said I can talk to him now.

303
00:16:48,167 --> 00:16:49,733
Wait a second, Ma'am...

304
00:16:49,867 --> 00:16:51,500
does chief know?

305
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:55,133
He won't know unless
you tell him.

306
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:00,633
You're such a meddler,
you know that?

307
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,800
You love interfering!

308
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:06,433
Dad, if I hadn't stepped in
between you and Ninong Victor,

309
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:08,433
you two would've clashed.

310
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,467
What are you thinking?

311
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,133
You think I can't handle him?
Like that?

312
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,433
Dad, I'm sorry, okay?

313
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:17,700
I was just thinking
about your candidacy.

314
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,300
Ninong Victor's name is
everywhere...

315
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:21,367
he's a popular actor.

316
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,900
And based on our surveys,

317
00:17:24,033 --> 00:17:25,100
he's getting a lot of support.

318
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:26,700
I don't care about surveys!

319
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,467
I don't believe in them!

320
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,867
And remember this...

321
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,400
I've been in politics
for 20 years .

322
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:35,200
Have I ever lost?

323
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:36,733
Huh? Have I lost?!

324
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:37,667
But, Dad...

325
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,533
Can you just be quiet?

326
00:17:39,667 --> 00:17:44,000
From now on,
stay out of my strategy.

327
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:48,967
Or maybe, you want to run
against me?

328
00:17:51,433 --> 00:17:53,500
Go on. Get out! Go!

329
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:55,067
Yes, Dad.

330
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:57,500
I'm sorry.

331
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:09,367
Just wait for Amo's arrival,
okay?

332
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,500
All right, thank you.

333
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:12,000
Thank you, thank you.

334
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:13,100
Thank you, Brother.

335
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:14,867
Oh, hi, Sergeant Enriquez.

336
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,933
I'm Berns, Amo's assistant.

337
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:19,033
Sorry, the set inside
is super busy,

338
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:22,133
And I'm sorry
but Amo canceled last minute.

339
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:23,833
There's just a lot
to handle right now

340
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:26,100
since he's starting to campaign.

341
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,867
I hope you understand.

342
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:30,467
- Is that so?
- Yes.

343
00:18:31,033 --> 00:18:32,267
It's okay.

344
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,167
As long as you can answer
my questions.

345
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,633
Well, I know everything there is
to know about Amo,

346
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:38,000
so you can ask me anything.

347
00:18:38,133 --> 00:18:39,733
What do you want to know?

348
00:18:40,167 --> 00:18:42,567
Are you familiar with the movie

349
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:44,400
"<i> The Boss and the Evil
Spirits</i> ?"

350
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:45,967
Of course.

351
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:48,100
That was one of the first movies
produced

352
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:49,867
by Amo's production company.

353
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,633
What do you need to know?

354
00:18:51,767 --> 00:18:54,567
In the movie,
the robbers used masks.

355
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,900
- Yes.
- This.

356
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:01,200
Do you know where
those masks are now?

357
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:03,867
Oh, those masks,
along with other movie props

358
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,367
Amo donated them to an exhibit.

359
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,567
Exhibit?

360
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:08,700
Where is this exhibit?

361
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:10,633
Calabari museum.

362
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,733
Amo is very generous.

363
00:19:12,867 --> 00:19:15,133
Yes, that's right,
Calabari museum.

364
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:16,133
Okay.

365
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:17,533
Do you need to ask
anything else?

366
00:19:17,667 --> 00:19:19,600
Sorry again, things are just
really hectic inside.

367
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:20,667
It's okay.

368
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,967
Thank you, Miss Berns.

369
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,567
- Thank you, Sergeant Enriquez.
- Thank you.

370
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,333
Nice to meet you.
Sorry.

371
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:30,767
Are there still missing items

372
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:32,900
from other sections of the
museum?

373
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:37,700
Everything they got from there,
we've recovered.

374
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:42,233
We also checked the valuable
items on display

375
00:19:42,367 --> 00:19:44,167
none of them are missing.

376
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,400
Okay.

377
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:47,900
What about Amo's masks?

378
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,567
What masks?

379
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,467
Oh, these.

380
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:56,900
These ones.

381
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,167
Amo's assistant said,

382
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,367
they were here
at the history museum.

383
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,500
Where are they?

384
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:08,433
Sorry, Ma'am, but it looks like
those were part

385
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,767
of Amo's things that haven't
been displayed yet

386
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,600
Mind if I check?

387
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,867
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

388
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:21,633
Stop pestering me unless
you want trouble.

389
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,733
- I already know about it.
- Again...

390
00:20:23,867 --> 00:20:25,200
Thank you, okay?

391
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,733
I'm busy.

392
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,300
Persistent.

393
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,000
Go answer your boyfriend.

394
00:20:37,133 --> 00:20:38,967
He might sulk.

395
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:41,133
Amo, he's not my boyfriend.

396
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:43,433
This is the cop
I told you about.

397
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,367
She's been calling nonstop.

398
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:49,667
Is she the one asking about my
movie props?

399
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,733
Yes, Amo. She's so annoying.

400
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:53,367
Oh, she's a cop,
then why aren't you answering?

401
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,633
Amo, because she kept asking
so many questions.

402
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:56,733
And when I asked

403
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:57,867
if it's part of an
investigation,

404
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
she wouldn't even tell me.

405
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:02,733
So I thought, maybe he's not
even really a cop.

406
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:04,500
Or she's just not
in the position

407
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,100
to tell you anything.

408
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:07,700
Here's the deal,
if she calls again,

409
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:10,133
answer it, I'll talk to her.

410
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:15,033
Oh, Amo...

411
00:21:20,467 --> 00:21:21,800
Hello, Miss Berns?

412
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:23,867
Sergeant, this is Victor.

413
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,433
Amo?

414
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:27,067
Idol!

415
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:29,333
Is that really you?

416
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:31,167
It's me.

417
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:33,100
How can I help you?

418
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:34,900
Amo, did you know

419
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:36,800
that items were stolen
from your exhibit

420
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:38,833
at the history museum?

421
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,667
Can you come here right now?

422
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:51,367
Joaquin!

423
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,233
I heard you yelled
at your son again!

424
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:57,133
So he told you?

425
00:21:57,267 --> 00:21:59,033
House help talk.

426
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:01,867
Joaquin, Glen is your heir!

427
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,033
You should be helping
your son rise up.

428
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:06,267
Why are you pulling him down?

429
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,767
He doesn't have an iron fist.

430
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,200
He's too kind!

431
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:14,333
Politics isn't just about
saying yes and smiling.

432
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:17,100
If he ever goes up against
Victor,

433
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,300
he'll be devoured whole!

434
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:32,400
Is Glen really the reason for
your bad temper?

435
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:39,133
He stole my role in the film.

436
00:22:39,267 --> 00:22:41,800
And I swear, someone will die

437
00:22:41,933 --> 00:22:45,367
if he takes
my current position too!

438
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,667
Sergeant Enriquez...

439
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:04,433
Amo...

440
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:09,067
Do I have something on my face?

441
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:12,800
No, no, Sir...

442
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:13,833
I'm sorry, Amo.

443
00:23:13,967 --> 00:23:16,567
I just can't believe

444
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:18,533
I'm standing in front of you.

445
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:21,200
I've idolized you
since I was a kid.

446
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:24,733
Are you saying I'm old?

447
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:27,967
Oh! No, Amo!

448
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,133
No, sorry!

449
00:23:30,267 --> 00:23:31,533
Relax, Sergeant.

450
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:33,067
That is a joke.

451
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:36,233
I know I'm getting old...

452
00:23:36,733 --> 00:23:39,600
but I can still run a marathon.

453
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:41,133
It's not obvious.

454
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:42,767
You look young.

455
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:46,867
Actually, Amo...

456
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:51,100
you're the reason
I became a cop.

457
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,533
Your movies...

458
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:56,900
they're one of the reasons

459
00:23:57,067 --> 00:23:59,867
I wanted to become
an investigator.

460
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:03,933
No matter where
you hide in hell,

461
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:06,433
Amo will come for you!

462
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:09,367
- Son of a duck.
- Son of a duck.

463
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,433
Oh...

464
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:16,800
What did your
investigation turn up?

465
00:24:17,233 --> 00:24:21,667
With all the props in the
museum,

466
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:24,800
I don't get why the thieves

467
00:24:24,933 --> 00:24:27,400
were interested
in the demonic masks.

468
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:30,667
To be honest,
I don't know their motive.

469
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:33,433
But, Amo, here.

470
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:37,100
Look at this.

471
00:24:38,667 --> 00:24:41,967
Your masks were used
in a bank robbery.

472
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,933
Which means, the same group
that broke

473
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:48,767
into the museum also broke the
San Isidro Rural Bank.

474
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:52,467
Then they need to be caught
as soon as possible.

475
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:55,600
Wait...

476
00:24:56,967 --> 00:24:59,933
Here, that's my personal number.

477
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:06,400
If I can help in your
investigation, just call me.

478
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:08,233
All right, Amo. Thank you.

479
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:10,167
- I'll go ahead, okay.
- Okay.

480
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:13,000
Oh, Amo...

481
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:17,233
There's one more thing
I wanted to ask.

482
00:25:17,367 --> 00:25:18,533
What is it?

483
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:21,633
Can I take a picture with you?

484
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:24,367
- That's it? Sure, sure.
- You are my idol.

485
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,667
Come here.

486
00:25:28,167 --> 00:25:28,700
Okay.

487
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:29,800
- Thank you.
- Okay.

488
00:25:47,833 --> 00:25:50,233
Oh, Serge, what's that?

489
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:53,267
Amo's calling card.

490
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:55,200
He's actually
a really nice in person.

491
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:57,433
And still handsome.

492
00:25:58,833 --> 00:25:59,933
But, Serge...

493
00:26:00,067 --> 00:26:01,867
did you go there to investigate

494
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,600
or to get a selfie?

495
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,933
Of course, to investigate!

496
00:26:10,567 --> 00:26:14,433
He said he didn't know his mask
was stolen from the museum.

497
00:26:14,567 --> 00:26:16,867
You think
he is telling the truth?

498
00:26:24,267 --> 00:26:25,867
Let's just go.

499
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:16,833
Stop them!

500
00:27:17,633 --> 00:27:19,900
That's enough! We're police!

501
00:27:20,033 --> 00:27:21,767
Stay out of this!

502
00:27:30,433 --> 00:27:32,033
Lieutenant Conde?

503
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:35,467
At a time like this,

504
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,567
you should be coming out
already.

505
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:38,533
- What?
- What?

506
00:27:38,667 --> 00:27:40,433
I know you're very eager

507
00:27:40,567 --> 00:27:42,000
to be your dad's running mate.

508
00:27:42,133 --> 00:27:45,500
And I also know I'm the only
true heir of dad

509
00:27:45,633 --> 00:27:47,167
when it comes to politics.

510
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:49,433
You do know that's my spot you
were lying on, right?

511
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:50,333
I don't even know

512
00:27:50,467 --> 00:27:51,967
how I got there, okay?

513
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:52,900
And I'm a cop!

514
00:27:53,033 --> 00:27:54,833
Let's say he
is involved somehow,

515
00:27:54,967 --> 00:27:55,967
but why would they steal?

516
00:27:56,100 --> 00:27:57,333
He's running for office, right?

517
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:59,400
He'd need
a bigger campaign budget.

518
00:27:59,533 --> 00:28:00,667
I need to speak with the Chief.

519
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,300
- Sir.
- What are you doing here?

520
00:28:02,433 --> 00:28:04,133
Lieutenant Conde,
I'm assigned here now.
